1. Download pytesseract from here and follow the steps to install it: https://github.com/UB-Mannheim/tesseract/wiki

2. Create new project interpreter in conda environment

3. pip install --upgrade pip

4. pip install pdf2image

5. pip install opencv-python

6. pip install pytesseract

7. pip install pdfkit

8. Conda: conda install -c conda-forge poppler
   Mac: brew install poppler
   Archlinux: sudo pacman -S poppler
   Ubuntu: sudo apt-get install poppler-utils

9. pip install pyttsx3

10. Download wkhtmltopdf here: https://wkhtmltopdf.org/downloads.html

11. Drag entire folder, usually in C:/Users/[USER], into pycharm project, usually in C:/Users/[USER]/PycharmProjects/[PROJECT NAME]

12. Change filepath in @turnToImage.py to the location in drive. Keep "wkhtmltopdf/bin/wkhtmltopdf.exe"

13. Change all the the arjoo directories to the current user in these files: turnToImage, makeText, pdfFileDownload

14. Run main.py after adding link to NY Times article

15. Set project encoding to windows-1252 (open bodyText file in TextFiles after running main, and click message at top)